stateDiagram-v2
    %% Manual Summary - State Machine Diagram
    %% Based on actual ManualSummary.tsx implementation

    [*] --> INITIALIZING

    %% Initial component mount
    INITIALIZING --> LOADING : componentDidMount()\n[useEffect runs generate()]

    %% Generation process
    LOADING --> HAS_SUMMARY : generateManualSummary()\n[summaryData populated && messages > 0]
    LOADING --> NO_MESSAGES : generateManualSummary()\n[summaryData populated && messages === 0]

    %% Time range changes (from any state except loading)
    HAS_SUMMARY --> LOADING : handlePreset()\n[new time range selected]
    NO_MESSAGES --> LOADING : handlePreset()\n[new time range selected]

    %% Close transitions (from any state)
    INITIALIZING --> [*] : onClose()\n[Escape/backdrop click]
    LOADING --> [*] : onClose()\n[Escape/backdrop click]
    HAS_SUMMARY --> [*] : onClose()\n[Escape/backdrop click]
    NO_MESSAGES --> [*] : onClose()\n[Escape/backdrop click]

    %% State definitions and transitions
    note right of INITIALIZING
        **State Definitions:**
        INITIALIZING: Component mounted, setting up portal
        LOADING: Generating summary, showing spinner
        HAS_SUMMARY: Summary ready, displaying results
        NO_MESSAGES: No messages found in time range

        **Key State Variables:**
        isGenerating: boolean (true during LOADING)
        summaryData: null or SummaryData object
        selectedHours: 0.5 | 1 | 3 (time range)

        **Transition Triggers:**
        componentDidMount: Initial render
        handlePreset: Time range button clicked
        onClose: Escape key or backdrop click
    end note
